<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>Email Verification</title>
</head>
<body style="margin: 0; padding: 0; background-color: white; width: 100%;">
  <div style="display: flex;flex-direction: column;justify-content: center; align-items: center; height: 80vh; width: 100%; background-color:white">
    <div style="color: #000;background-color:#F7F4ED; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content:between;align-items: center;border:#000 solid 2px;padding:10px 14px;border-radius:10px">
      <ul style="color: #000; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; list-style: none;">
        <li style="font-size: 34px ;font-weight: bold; text-align: center;">Medium.</li>
        <li style="font-size: 22px; text-align: center;">Your login link</li>
        <li style="font-size: 20px; text-align: center;">Click the link below to sign in to your Medium account.</li>
        <li style="font-size: 20px; text-align: center;">This link will expire in 2 hours and can only be used once.</li>
        <li style="font-size: 20px; text-align: center;color:#F7F4ED ;background-color:black ;font-size:16px ;border-radius: 20px;padding:10px 20px;cursor:pointer;align-self:center">Sign in to Medium</li>
        <li style="text-align: center;">If the button above doesn't work, paste this link into your web browser: 
          <a href="{{link}}" style="color: #dc2626;">{{link}}</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p style="font-size: 14px; text-align: center; color: #919191;">
        Click “Sign up” to agree to Medium's Terms of Service and acknowledge that Medium's Privacy Policy applies to you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
